{"parentUuid":"be22af56-2ccf-4604-8885-eba6891459dd","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\src\\src-darren\\model-repo","sessionId":"5338318a-31d4-4ee2-aa72-0c4237983907","version":"2.1.23","gitBranch":"main","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: C:\\Users\\darren\\.claude\\skills\\taskmaster\n\n# 🎯 TaskMaster - Install & Manage Task Master AI\n\nTask Master AI is a task management system for AI-driven development that integrates with Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, and other AI-enabled editors.\n\n**Official Resources:**\n- Website: https://www.task-master.dev/\n- GitHub: https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master\n- NPM: https://www.npmjs.com/package/task-master-ai\n\n## 🚀 Quick Actions\n\nWhen user invokes this skill, determine their intent and execute the appropriate action:\n\n| User Intent | Action |\n|-------------|--------|\n| \"install taskmaster\" | Run fresh install |\n| \"update taskmaster\" | Update to latest version |\n| \"taskmaster version\" | Show installed version |\n| \"init taskmaster\" | Initialize in current project |\n| \"taskmaster status\" | Check installation and config status |\n| Just \"/taskmaster\" | Show interactive menu |\n\n## 📦 Installation Methods\n\n### Method 1: NPM Global Install (Recommended)\n\nTo install Task Master globally:\n\n```bash\nnpm install -g task-master-ai\n```\n\nTo verify installation:\n\n```bash\ntask-master --version\n```\n\n### Method 2: Claude Code MCP Integration\n\nTo add Task Master as an MCP server in Claude Code:\n\n```bash\nclaude mcp add taskmaster-ai -- npx -y task-master-ai\n```\n\n### Method 3: Local Project Install\n\nTo install in a specific project:\n\n```bash\nnpm install task-master-ai\n```\n\n## 🔄 Update Process\n\nTo update Task Master to the latest version:\n\n```bash\n# Check current version\ntask-master --version 2>/dev/null || npx task-master-ai --version\n\n# Update globally installed version\nnpm update -g task-master-ai\n\n# Or reinstall to force latest\nnpm install -g task-master-ai@latest\n\n# Verify new version\ntask-master --version\n```\n\nTo check what version is available on npm:\n\n```bash\nnpm show task-master-ai version\n```\n\n## 🏗️ Project Initialization\n\nTo initialize Task Master in a new or existing project:\n\n```bash\n# Basic initialization\ntask-master init\n\n# Initialize with AI editor rules\ntask-master init --rules cursor,windsurf,vscode\n\n# Add rules to existing installation\ntask-master rules add cursor,windsurf,vscode,roo\n```\n\nAfter initialization, the following structure is created:\n\n```\n.taskmaster/\n├── config.json          # Configuration file\n├── tasks/               # Task storage\n│   └── tasks.json       # Task data\n└── docs/                # Documentation\n    └── prd.txt          # Product Requirements Document\n```\n\n## 📋 Common Commands\n\n### Task Management\n\n```bash\n# List all tasks\ntask-master list\n\n# Show next task to work on\ntask-master next\n\n# Show specific tasks\ntask-master show 1,3,5\n\n# Move task between states\ntask-master move --from=5 --from-tag=backlog --to-tag=in-progress\n\n# Expand a task into subtasks\ntask-master expand task 4\n```\n\n### PRD Parsing\n\n```bash\n# Parse a PRD file to generate tasks\ntask-master parse-prd .taskmaster/docs/prd.txt\n\n# Or from alternate location\ntask-master parse-prd scripts/prd.txt\n```\n\n### Research\n\n```bash\n# Research a topic with context\ntask-master research \"JWT authentication best practices\"\n```\n\n## ⚙️ Configuration\n\n### API Keys Setup\n\nTask Master requires at least one AI provider API key. Set in environment or `.env`:\n\n```bash\n# Required: At least one of these\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...\nOPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\n\n# Optional: Additional providers\nGOOGLE_API_KEY=...\nPERPLEXITY_API_KEY=...\nXAI_API_KEY=...\n```\n\n**Note:** When using Claude Code CLI, no API key is needed as it uses Claude Code's authentication.\n\n### MCP Configuration for Editors\n\n**Cursor/Windsurf** (`~/.cursor/mcp.json`):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"task-master-ai\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"-y\", \"task-master-ai\"],\n      \"env\": {\n        \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\": \"your-key\",\n        \"OPENAI_API_KEY\": \"your-key\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**VS Code** (`.vscode/mcp.json`):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"task-master-ai\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"-y\", \"task-master-ai\"],\n      \"env\": {\n        \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\": \"your-key\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Tool Loading Optimization\n\nControl MCP tool loading via `TASK_MASTER_TOOLS` environment variable:\n\n| Mode | Tools | Token Usage | Use Case |\n|------|-------|-------------|----------|\n| `all` | 36 | ~21,000 | Full functionality |\n| `standard` | 15 | ~10,000 | Balanced |\n| `core` | 7 | ~5,000 | Minimal context |\n| `custom` | Variable | Variable | Specific tools only |\n\n## 🔍 Troubleshooting\n\n### Check Installation Status\n\nTo diagnose Task Master installation:\n\n```bash\n# Check if globally installed\nnpm list -g task-master-ai 2>/dev/null || echo \"Not globally installed\"\n\n# Check available version\nnpm show task-master-ai version\n\n# Check if command is available\nwhich task-master 2>/dev/null || where task-master 2>/dev/null || echo \"Command not in PATH\"\n\n# Try running via npx\nnpx task-master-ai --version\n```\n\n### Common Issues\n\n**\"command not found\":**\n- Reinstall globally: `npm install -g task-master-ai`\n- Or use npx: `npx task-master-ai <command>`\n\n**Permission errors on Windows:**\n- Run terminal as Administrator\n- Or use `npm install -g task-master-ai --force`\n\n**Outdated version:**\n- Clear npm cache: `npm cache clean --force`\n- Reinstall: `npm install -g task-master-ai@latest`\n\n## 📊 Execution Flow\n\nWhen this skill is invoked:\n\n1. **Detect intent** from user input\n2. **Check current state:**\n   - Is Task Master installed?\n   - What version?\n   - Is current directory a Task Master project?\n3. **Execute appropriate action:**\n   - Install if not present\n   - Update if requested\n   - Initialize project if requested\n4. **Report results** with version info and next steps\n\n## 🎯 Interactive Menu\n\nWhen invoked without specific intent, present this menu:\n\n```\n🎯 TaskMaster Management\n\nWhat would you like to do?\n\n1. 📦 Install Task Master (npm install -g task-master-ai)\n2. 🔄 Update Task Master (npm update -g task-master-ai)\n3. 📋 Check Version (task-master --version)\n4. 🏗️ Initialize in Current Project (task-master init)\n5. 🔍 Check Installation Status (diagnostics)\n6. ⚙️ Configure MCP for Editor (Cursor/VS Code/Windsurf)\n\nEnter number or describe what you need:\n```\n\n## 📝 Notes\n\n- Task Master uses MIT License with Commons Clause\n- Works with Claude 3.7/4 and other AI models\n- Integrates with `.specify/` workflow if present\n- Creates `.taskmaster/` directory for project data\n- Safe to run multiple times - idempotent operations\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"96ef7a05-de65-4877-ab46-67feb02a895c","timestamp":"2026-01-30T13:36:04.929Z"}
