{"parentUuid":"c8dec884-5db8-49bd-bf31-6af3d7aff2a1","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\src\\src-darren\\model-repo","sessionId":"5338318a-31d4-4ee2-aa72-0c4237983907","version":"2.1.23","gitBranch":"main","slug":"partitioned-growing-hopper","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: C:\\Users\\darren\\.claude\\skills\\zwrapup\n\n# zwrapup - Wrap Up AI Session\n\nComprehensive session cleanup that commits work, documents progress, and maintains clean git state.\n\n## What it does\n\nThis skill will:\n\n1. **Analyze session changes**:\n   - Check git status for all uncommitted changes\n   - Count modified, staged, and new files\n   - Generate intelligent commit message based on changes\n\n2. **Update RESUME.md**:\n   - Append session summary with timestamp\n   - List files changed\n   - Note key accomplishments\n   - Track session metadata\n\n3. **Commit everything**:\n   - Stage all changes (including RESUME.md)\n   - Create descriptive commit message\n   - Include Claude Code attribution\n\n4. **Push to remotes**:\n   - Push to `origin` (git.superpowerlabs.app)\n   - Push to `alt`/`pool` (Synology NAS) if configured\n\n5. **Clean up branches**:\n   - Delete local branches merged into main/master\n   - Skip protected branches (main, master, develop)\n   - Skip current branch\n   - Report cleaned branches\n\n## Usage\n\nRun this at the end of any AI-assisted coding session:\n\n```bash\n/zwrapup\n```\n\nOr manually execute:\n\n```bash\nbash ~/.claude/skills/zwrapup/zwrapup.sh\n```\n\n## What gets committed\n\n- All modified files\n- All new untracked files\n- Updated RESUME.md with session notes\n- Commit message format: `Session YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM - [brief summary]`\n\n## Branch cleanup rules\n\n**Will delete:**\n- Local branches fully merged into main/master\n- Old feature branches no longer needed\n\n**Will NOT delete:**\n- Current branch\n- main, master, develop\n- Branches with unmerged commits\n- Remote-only branches\n\n## Output example\n\n```\n=== zwrapup - Wrap Up Session ===\n\n[1/5] Analyzing changes...\n  → 3 modified, 0 staged, 2 new files\n\n[2/5] Updating RESUME.md...\n  ✓ Added session entry\n\n[3/5] Committing changes...\n  ✓ Committed: Session 2026-01-05 22:45 - Fixed dashboard UI issues\n\n[4/5] Pushing to remotes...\n  ✓ Pushed to origin\n  ✓ Pushed to pool\n\n[5/5] Cleaning up branches...\n  ✓ Deleted: feature/old-experiment (merged)\n  ✓ Deleted: bugfix/temp-fix (merged)\n  → Skipped 2 unmerged branches\n\n=== Session Complete ===\nAll changes committed and pushed!\n```\n\n## Script location\n\n`~/.claude/skills/zwrapup/zwrapup.sh`\n\n## Notes\n\n- Safe to run multiple times (idempotent)\n- RESUME.md created if it doesn't exist\n- Works with both origin and alt/pool remotes\n- Only deletes branches that are fully merged\n- Preserves work-in-progress branches\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"de541cbe-9cd3-4eb1-a599-8212a5144c70","timestamp":"2026-01-30T16:01:06.331Z"}
